                When I was younger my father drove me to all my tennis matches.
                On the way back he would tell me about the things I did right and wrongâ€¦ but mostly the things I did wrong. 
                Being the stubborn kid I am, I wouldn't believe him and eventually he started 
                bringing a clipboard to tally my match statistics.
                That was a long time ago, and while there are many tennis tracker apps out there now that could've replaced that clipboard, 
                they are all either limited in features or require one to pay for full functionality.
              </p>              
