          <div class="col">
            <div id="section_header">
              <h3>What This App Does:</h3>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class = "row">
          <div class="col">
            <div class="text_whitebg">
              <p>
                This completely-free tennis statistics app allows users to track various data points of a match: aces, winners, unforced errors, etc.
                Based of this, the app displays match statistics allowing users to gain key insight into their matches. 
              </p>
              <p>
                Tennis Stats has online functionality as well. Users can create, save, and retrieve matches all via a cloud account. 
                This ensures matches will never be lost and lets users share matches across multiple devices.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <br>
    
    <section class="explain_part">
      <div class="container">
        <div class = "row">
          <div class="col">
            <div id="section_header">
              <h3>What I Learned:</h3>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class = "row">
          <div class="col">
            <div class="text_whitebg">
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Android App Development:</strong> This was my first time making an Android App. I learned how to use activities, fragments, adapters, interfaces and how to communicate between them.</li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Firebase:</strong> This was also my first exposure to Firebase. I learned how to save, download, delete and upload files to the Firebase Storage. 
                  I also learned how properly structure the database allowing for efficient retrieval and syncing of information.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Layouts and xml:</strong> I learned how to use the various android layouts and views to create an intuitive user interface. </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
